    {
      "parameters": {
        "agent": "conversationalAgent",
        "promptType": "define",
        "text": "=🧠 Step 1: Summarize the Email Conversation.\nThe email conversation is in these inputs -> {{ $json.text }},{{ $json.Conversation }} and {{ $json.from_email }}{{ $json.to_emails }}{{ $json.cc_emails }}\nObjective: Generate a concise summary capturing the key points, tone, and relevant details.\n\nOutput Format should contain the following fields as separate json items:\n\n1. Participants: List of people involved.\n\n2. Issue Summary: One-paragraph description of the core discussion/problem.\n\n3. Timeline: Brief overview of the progression of the conversation.\n\n4. Tone Detection: Note if the tone is frustrated, urgent, confused, neutral, etc.\n\n5. Already Resolved?: Yes/No\n\n6. Issue question: Generate additional output item with detailed explanation of the issue experienced as a question so it can be sent to a Knowledge base AI\n\n🔍 Step 2: Identify and Estimate the Issue\nIssue Extraction:\n\nUse language patterns to detect keywords like problem, error, delay, can’t, issue, unexpected, etc.\n\nClassify the issue using common support categories (e.g., login issue, API failure, payment issue).\n\nConfidence Estimation: Assign a confidence score or flag if the issue type is ambiguous.",
